products.facts: ["Creamy peanut butter is primarily made from ground roasted peanuts, often with added oils and sweeteners for texture and flavor.","Peanut farming can be beneficial for soil health as peanuts are legumes that fix nitrogen in the soil, reducing the need for chemical fertilizers.","Many brands of creamy peanut butter offer natural options that contain no added sugars or hydrogenated oils, focusing on pure peanut content.","The production of peanut butter has a lower carbon footprint compared to other nut butters, making it a more sustainable choice for consumers."]
